cat: pearls must be strung to be treasure
even a sheet of paper is lighter together
when whales fight, the shrimp gets hurt
the frog forgets its tadpole days
dust piles up into a mountain
tap even a stone bridge before crossing
enter the tiger's den to catch a cub
using a rake for what a hoe could stop
the day you go is market day
habits formed at three last until eighty
stay true to your first resolve
a needle thief becomes a cow thief
like hitting a rock with an egg
eating rice cakes while lying down
other people's rice cakes look bigger
a word repays a thousand nyang of debt
eat the pheasant and its egg
swimming with feet on the ground
fix the barn after losing the cow
the trusted axe cuts your foot
the fuller the rice, the lower it bows
seeing once beats hearing a hundred times
can't name even giyeok with a sickle
too many boatmen steer the boat astray
